## *Where* are motor signals integrated?

![](images/people/GabbyButler.jpeg){.absolute bottom=10 right=10 width="100" height="100"}


- Frequency-following response (FFR) shows the fidelity of incoming sound encoding
- If integration is subcortical, would expect to see FFR differences between self-generated vs. passive sound
- No FFR differences, despite cortical response differences
- Motor signals unlikely to attenuate earliest central auditory signals

